<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 5:04PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Marion,
northwestern Winston, northwestern Fayette and northern Lamar
Counties through 545 PM CDT...
At 504 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Phil Campbell to near Hackleburg to Hamilton to
near New Wren. Movement was south at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Winfield, Haleyville, Vernon, Sulligent, Guin, Brilliant, Glen Allen,
Detroit, Beaverton, Gu-
Win, Lamar County Airport, Lake Buttahatchee, Needmore, Crews,
Bedford, Twin, Gattman, Natural Bridge, Tucker and Henson Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
